Enum SelectableBehavior.ObjectState

    Enclosing class:
    SelectableBehavior

    public static enum SelectableBehavior.ObjectState
extends java.lang.Enum<SelectableBehavior.ObjectState>
    Define all possible states the SelectableBehavior can be in

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      BEHIND
      This state means that a Cursor is behind the associated GVRSceneObject.
      CLICKED
      This state means that a Cursor is intersecting with the associated GVRSceneObject and CursorEvent.isActive returns true.
      COLLIDING
      This state means that a Cursor is intersecting with the associated GVRSceneObject It is recommended that the appearance of the associated GVRSceneObject in this state changes from the DEFAULT to make the user aware of a collision.
      DEFAULT
      The state in which the SelectableBehavior is initially.
      SCALE
      This state means that two Cursors have selected this GVRSceneObject it will be scaled based on the relative distance between these two Cursors

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • DEFAULT

        public static final SelectableBehavior.ObjectState DEFAULT
        The state in which the SelectableBehavior is initially. This represents the normal appearance of the associated GVRSceneObject

      • BEHIND

        public static final SelectableBehavior.ObjectState BEHIND
        This state means that a Cursor is behind the associated GVRSceneObject. Recommended appearance of the associated GVRSceneObject in this state is a wire frame or a transparent texture, to allow the Cursor to be visible to the user.

      • COLLIDING

        public static final SelectableBehavior.ObjectState COLLIDING
        This state means that a Cursor is intersecting with the associated GVRSceneObject It is recommended that the appearance of the associated GVRSceneObject in this state changes from the DEFAULT to make the user aware of a collision.

      • CLICKED

        public static final SelectableBehavior.ObjectState CLICKED
        This state means that a Cursor is intersecting with the associated GVRSceneObject and CursorEvent.isActive returns true. It is recommended that the appearance of the associated GVRSceneObject in this state changes from the DEFAULT to make the user aware of the clicked state.

      • SCALE

        public static final SelectableBehavior.ObjectState SCALE
        This state means that two Cursors have selected this GVRSceneObject it will be scaled based on the relative distance between these two Cursors
